This paper proposes a dynamic network embedding method that addresses the challenges of applying static network embedding in dynamic settings. The paper focuses on network representation learning, which falls under the category of machine learning and data mining. The paper also discusses the use of evolving random walks and initialization of current graph embedding with previous embedding vectors, which are techniques commonly used in network science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
